-- Kapsch TrafficCom Consortium Wins $1.7 Billion Polish Highway Toll Tender
-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 2010-10-03T14:19:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/kapsch-trafficcom-consortium-wins-1-7-billion-polish-highway-toll-tender.html
Kapsch TrafficCom AG , the Austrian
maker of toll systems, said it won a tender for the installation
and operation of an electronic toll collection system for a
Polish highway.  The project was awared by the  Polish Directorate for
National Roads and Highways  to a consortium led by Kapsch late
on Oct. 1, according to a statement today.  The Kapsch consortium offered a system for a price of 4.9
billion zloty ($1.7 billion), the Vienna-based company said in
the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  